# Ansible Best Practices Dashboard - Changelog
# Format: Version | Date | Changes

================================================================================
v0.0.1 | 2025-12-28 | Initial dashboard creation
================================================================================
- Created interactive HTML dashboard for tracking 71 Ansible best practice issues
- Implemented issue categorization by severity (Critical Breaking, Architecture, Security, etc.)
- Added priority-based filtering system (8 severity categories)
- Included phase timeline with 7 implementation phases
- Created localStorage-based progress persistence
- Added 6 impact metric cards:
  * Code Reduction (-87.8%)
  * Code Duplication (-93.7%)
  * Maintainability Score (+500%)
  * Reliability Improvement (+216%)
  * Performance Gain (+300-500%)
  * Security Vulnerabilities Fixed (100%)
- Implemented expandable issue details with sub-item breakdowns
- Added Chart.js visualizations for severity distribution
- Created responsive grid layout with gradient header
- Included completion tracking (0/71 issues, 0/159 sub-items)
- Added stats dashboard (41 critical issues, 28 security issues)
- Implemented 7-phase project timeline with time estimates

================================================================================
v0.1.0 | 2025-12-28 | Four major feature enhancements
================================================================================
Feature 1: Independent Sub-Item Progress Tracking
- Fixed parent checkbox behavior to preserve individual sub-item states
- Parent checkboxes no longer override child completion status
- Parent auto-checks only when ALL children are completed
- Partial completion keeps parent unchecked
- Modified toggleCompletion() function (lines 1322-1355)

Feature 2: Code Snippet Viewing
- Added "View Code" buttons to sub-items with code examples
- Implemented collapsible code snippets with line numbers
- Added syntax highlighting for problematic code lines
- Created dark theme code viewer (#1F2937 background)
- Highlighted offending lines in red (rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.2))
- Added sample code for 5 key issues:
  * Issue 3-1: Hardcoded username "dgarner"
  * Issue 3-2: User-specific power management paths
  * Issue 5-1: Twingate curl|bash installation
  * Issue 5-2: Docker GPG curl|bash pattern
  * Issue 7-1: Wildcard package upgrades with ignore_errors
- Implemented toggleCodeSnippet() function (lines 1456-1462)
- Added CSS styling for code snippets (lines 480-533)

Feature 3: Full-Width Impact Modals
- Replaced inline expansion with modal overlay system
- Created 1000px max-width modal dialogs
- Added click-outside-to-close functionality
- Implemented smooth slide-in animation (@keyframes modalSlideIn)
- Created detailed modal content for all 6 impact types:
  * "What This Means" - metric definitions
  * "Why This Happens" - root cause analysis
  * "Contributing Issues" - which issues affect this metric
  * "Benefits" - practical advantages
- Added modal HTML structure (lines 851-861)
- Created modal CSS styling (lines 309-404)
- Implemented showImpactModal() and closeModal() functions (lines 1464-1478)

Feature 4: Dynamic Impact Calculations
- Implemented real-time metric recalculation based on completed issues
- Created weighted calculation system:
  * Code Reduction: Issue #6 (87.8%), Issue #9 (5%), Issue #7 (3%)
  * Code Duplication: Issue #6 (70%), #7 (15%), #9 (5%), #28 (3.7%)
  * Maintainability: 20 issues contribute proportionally
  * Reliability: Issue #7 + issues #24-33
  * Performance: Issue #34 (+100% bonus), #28, #35, #37-41
  * Security: All 13 security issues (#5, #12-23)
- Added calculateImpact() function (lines 1358-1398)
- Integrated recalculateAll() orchestrator (lines 1401-1454)
- Metrics now update immediately when issues are checked/unchecked

